The '''pink-throated twinspot''' ('''''Hypargos margaritatus''''') is a small seed-eating bird in the family [[Estrildidae]]. It inhabits dry savanna and moist, subtropical/tropical (lowland) shrubland habitats near the southeast African coast in [[Mozambique]], [[South Africa]] and [[Eswatini]].  It has a large range, with an estimated global extent of occurrence of 160,000&nbsp;km<sup>2</sup>.<ref name="BirdLife2017">{{cite web|last1=BirdLife International|title=Species factsheet: Pink-throated Twinspot (Hypargos margaritatus)|url=http://datazone.birdlife.org/species/factsheet/pink-throated-twinspot-hypargos-margaritatus|website=datazone.birdlife.org|access-date=23 July 2017}}</ref>

